 <i>ffraw</i> ‘fair, fine, brisk’. Compare   Frampton  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Frampton","meanings":["English: habitational name from any of various places so called, of which there are several in Gloucestershire, one in Dorset and one in Lincolnshire. Most take the name from the Frome river in south Gloucestershire (which is probably from a British word meaning ‘fair, brisk’) + Old English <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’. One near Tewkesbury was originally named in Old English as <i>Frēolingtūn</i> ‘settlement associated with <i>Frēola</i>’, a short form of any of various compound personal names with the first element <i>frēo</i> ‘free’. Frampton in Lincolnshire probably gets its name from an Old English byname <i>Frameca</i> (a derivative of <i>fram</i> ‘valiant’) + <i>tūn</i>."]},{"name":"Froom","meanings":["English: variant of   Frome  .","German: from a short form of a personal name composed with Middle High German <i>vrom</i>, <i>vrum</i> ‘valiant, steadfast’ (see   Frommelt  )."]}]},{"name":"Alice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Adelaide  , representing an Old French spelling of a reduced form of Germanic <i>Adalheidis</i>. <i>Alice</i> and <i>Adelaide</i> were already regarded as distinct names in English during the medieval period. <i>Alice</i> enjoyed a surge of popularity in the 19th century and periods of favour ever since. It was the name of the central character of  Lewis Carroll's  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (  1865 ) and Through the Looking Glass (  1872 ), who was based on his child friend  Alice Liddell , daughter of the Dean of Christ Church, Oxford."],"variants":[{"name":"Alys","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Alice ."]},{"name":"Alis","meanings":["equivalent of <b>Alice</b> ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Alice Frome was born in 1064, in Frome, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, her father, Frome, was 20 and her mother, Frome, was 20. She had at least 1 son with Odard Dutton 1st Lord Dutton. She died in Keckwick, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1064–":"1064–Surnud","1064–Female":"1064–Surnud","1046–Male":"1046–Surnud","1086–1135":"1086–1135","1044–Male":"1044–Surnud","1044–Female":"1044–Surnud","1135":"1135","1046":"1046","1044":"1044","1064":"1064","1086":"1086","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England","Frome, Somersetshire, England":"Frome, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Keckwick, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Keckwick, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1064–":"1064–Kuollut","1064–Female":"1064–Kuollut","1046–Male":"1046–Kuollut","1086–1135":"1086–1135","1044–Male":"1044–Kuollut","1044–Female":"1044–Kuollut","1135":"1135","1046":"1046","1044":"1044","1064":"1064","1086":"1086","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England","Frome, Somersetshire, England":"Frome, Somerset, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Keckwick, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Keckwick, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1064–":"1064–Décédée","1064–Female":"1064–Décédée","1046–Male":"1046–Décédé","1086–1135":"1086–1135","1044–Male":"1044–Décédé","1044–Female":"1044–Décédée","1135":"1135","1046":"1046","1044":"1044","1064":"1064","1086":"1086","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Angleterre","Frome, Somersetshire, England":"Frome, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Keckwick, Runcorn, Cheshire, England":"Keckwick, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Lady Alice Frome est née en 1064, à Frome, Somerset, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Frome, avait 20 ans et sa mère, Frome, avait 20 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Odard Dutton 1st Lord Dutton. Elle est décédée à Keckwick, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1064–":"1064–Verstorben","1064–Female":"1064–Verstorben","1046–Male":"1046–Verstorben","1086–1135":"1086–1135","1044–Male":"1044–Verstorben","1044–Female":"1044–Verstorben","1135":"1135","10